definitions.definition: Having to do with digits (fingers or toes); especially, performed with a finger.
Property of representing values as discrete , often binary , numbers rather than a continuous spectrum.
Of or relating to computers or the Information Age .
examples: Digital payment systems are replacing cash transactions.
